## Architecture map

```
src/
  index.ts                  entrypoint — reads data-* from script tag, mounts at document.body
  types.ts                  Thread, Comment, AnchorData, ResolvedAnchor, Identity, WidgetConfig
  styles.css                ALL styles scoped under #__comment-widget-root with cw- prefix
  components/
    CommentOverlay.vue      root component, owns: comment-mode, draft, active thread, deferred-identity actions, error state
    CommentPin.vue          single pin marker (24px tilted droplet)
    CommentThread.vue       popover w/ replies, resolve/reopen button, error banners
    IdentityPrompt.vue      first-write name+email modal
    Toolbar.vue             bottom-right floating button: count + filter funnel + comment toggle
  composables/
    useSupabase.ts          createSupabaseClient, subscribeToProject (postgres_changes on threads + comments)
    useIdentity.ts          localStorage-backed identity (key: __comment_widget_identity)
    useAnchoring.ts         Vue glue over AnchorScheduler — emits reactive position map
    useThreads.ts           CRUD + realtime merge, throws WidgetError on failure with translated hints
  lib/
    selectorPath.ts         computeSelectorPath (id > [data-comment-anchor] > tag:nth-of-type), resolveSelectorPath w/ progressive shortening fallback
    anchoring.ts            AnchorScheduler (shared MutationObserver + scroll/resize), AnchorWatcher (per-pin ResizeObserver)

supabase/
  schema.sql                threads + comments + indexes + RLS + realtime publication; idempotent
  README.md                 setup + security hardening checklist

demo/
  index.html                local test page w/ §7.5 failure-mode controls and project-switcher
  README.md                 acceptance walkthrough

.github/workflows/
  build-dist.yml            on push to main → npm run build → commits dist/widget.iife.js + widget.es.js back to main
  release.yml               on push of v* tag → verifies dist/ present → creates GitHub Release w/ assets
```

## Conventions

- **Vue 3 Composition API only.** No Options API anywhere — the `__VUE_OPTIONS_API__: false` flag in `vite.config.ts` tree-shakes it out.
- **TypeScript strict.** `noUnusedLocals` and `noUnusedParameters` are on; the build will fail on dead identifiers.
- **All styles scoped** under `#__comment-widget-root` with `cw-` prefixes. **Never** use bare element selectors (`button { }`) — they'd leak into the host page.
- **Sentence case in UI strings.** Per build plan §13. Never Title Case.
- **No narrative code comments** ("// increment the counter"). Comments only for non-obvious intent, trade-offs, or constraints the code itself can't convey.
- **Errors throw, callers translate.** `useThreads` throws `WidgetError` with a translated `hint`; UI components show `hint` inline. Don't ever swallow Supabase errors silently — that's what cost us a session earlier.
- **Optimistic updates with rollback.** `updateThreadStatus` flips local state first, awaits server, rolls back on error. Apply the same pattern to any new mutation.
- **Anchoring uses percentages, not pixels.** A click at 50% × 50% of a button stays at 50% × 50% whether the button is 200 px wide or 600 px wide.

## Gotchas paid for in time

Don't re-pay these:

1. **Vite library mode does NOT replace `process.env.NODE_ENV`** by default. The IIFE bundle dies with `ReferenceError: process is not defined` the moment you load it in vanilla HTML. Fix is the `define` block in `vite.config.ts` — keep it there.
2. **CSS must be injected at runtime**, not emitted as a separate file. We use `vite-plugin-css-injected-by-js` v3.5.x (v5+ requires Vite >8). Without this, consuming sites would need to load `widget.css` separately, breaking the "one script tag" embed pattern.
3. **`@supabase/supabase-js` is not tree-shakable past `createClient`** — it bundles auth + storage + functions + postgrest + realtime as one unit. That's ~50 KB of our ~88 KB gzipped bundle. The path to <80 KB if it ever matters: swap for direct `@supabase/postgrest-js` + `@supabase/realtime-js`.
4. **Realtime subscription filters can't OR across columns.** `comments` are subscribed without a server-side filter; the client filters by known `thread_id` membership in `useThreads.handleCommentEvent`.
5. **Permissive RLS policies** (`using (true)`) ship in `supabase/schema.sql`. This is intentional for MVP behind stakeholder-only URLs, but **must be tightened before any non-preview deployment**. Hardening checklist is in `supabase/README.md`.
6. **`document.currentScript` is null in ES modules.** The widget's auto-mount uses classic-script context; module consumers must call `window.CommentWidget.mount(config)` explicitly.
7. **Release ritual sequencing:** push to main → wait for `build-dist` workflow → `git pull` → tag → push tag. Skipping the pull means tagging a commit that pre-dates the bot's `dist/` commit, and jsDelivr will 404. The `release.yml` workflow verifies and fails loudly if so.

## Release flow

1. Code changes → push to `main`.
2. `build-dist` workflow runs, commits `build: refresh dist/ [skip ci]` back to main.
3. `git pull`, then `git tag vX.Y.Z && git push origin vX.Y.Z`.
4. `release` workflow runs, creates GitHub Release with assets.
5. Consuming sites bump the version in their `<script src="cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/USER/comment-widget@vX.Y.Z/dist/widget.iife.js">` tag.

**Always pin to exact tags on consumers**, never `@latest` — jsDelivr caches per-tag and `@latest` will silently break stakeholders.

## Roadmap (Phase 3 candidates, prioritized)

- **Slack webhook on new threads** — per-project webhook URL configured in Supabase, edge function bridges from `postgres_changes`.
- **Magic-link auth replacing localStorage identity** — drops the permissive RLS policies, restricts updates to row creator. The bigger lift.
- **Archive view** — list of resolved threads from past N days; soft-delete vs hard-delete decision still open.
- **Story-navigation auto-reload for Storybook embeds** — currently the widget mounts once per iframe and doesn't follow story changes; needs `popstate` + history monkey-patch to re-scope by URL.
- **Bundle slim to <80 KB gzipped** — modular Supabase imports (see gotcha #3).
- **Visible "approximate anchor" tooltip** — currently the dashed amber border is the only signal; a hover tooltip would help.

